-- Siemens makes $3.5 billion software buy
-- 
-- Wed Jan 24, 2007 7:41pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/25/us-siemens-portfolio-idUSWEB138520070125

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - German industrial conglomerate Siemens ( SIEGn.DE ) has agreed to buy U.S. software maker UGS Corp. for $3.5 billion and plans an initial public offering of its automotive engineering unit, VDO, it said on Wednesday. 

 Siemens said in a statement the acquisition of UGS would add industrial software for planning, design and simulation to its the automation-technology portfolio of its factory-automation unit, A&D. It added that it would begin preparations immediately for an IPO of VDO, which would give that business additional financial resources and flexibility for future growth.